WEBVTT

00:10.500 --> 00:13.150
13 billion years
ago the universe

00:13.150 --> 00:15.640
exploded into
existence, expanded out

00:15.640 --> 00:18.360
in every direction for
approximately a billion years,

00:18.360 --> 00:22.220
swirled itself into
100 trillion galaxies.

00:22.220 --> 00:24.230
Galaxies that
formed new elements

00:24.230 --> 00:25.700
in the hearts of their stars.

00:25.700 --> 00:28.140
Stars that exploded
with new element

00:28.140 --> 00:31.300
rich clouds of stellar
nebulae that could then

00:31.300 --> 00:33.350
swirl back into
second generation

00:33.350 --> 00:35.290
stars with planets around them.

00:35.290 --> 00:37.830
Planets with the inner
genius and creativity

00:37.830 --> 00:40.600
that they could bring forth
oceans and atmosphere,

00:40.600 --> 00:44.000
the first cells of life, all
of the creatures that we know.

00:44.000 --> 00:47.180
Every civilization, or every
culture, has a mythology.

00:47.180 --> 00:50.180
I remember the old story.
It goes like this—

00:50.590 --> 00:52.290
do you want to you hear this?

00:52.290 --> 00:53.830
It goes like this.

00:53.830 --> 00:56.480
That answers the basic
questions: Who are you?

00:56.480 --> 00:57.830
What is a human being?

00:57.830 --> 00:59.310
What's important in life?

00:59.310 --> 01:01.400
How does change
happen in the world?

01:01.400 --> 01:02.450
Where do we come from?

01:02.450 --> 01:04.200
Where are we going?

01:04.200 --> 01:09.720
The sky father had an affair
with the woman who is the sea.

01:09.720 --> 01:14.440
And there life began as
the single celled organism,

01:14.440 --> 01:15.980
the coral polyp.

01:15.980 --> 01:18.820
The Vedic science
story starts out

01:18.820 --> 01:21.640
the universe is consciousness
which slows down

01:21.640 --> 01:23.930
into matter and
everything therefore

01:23.930 --> 01:26.610
evolves within that
consciousness field.

01:26.610 --> 01:29.420
Life is a hoop.

01:29.420 --> 01:35.640
And every single life form
has one place on this hoop.

01:35.640 --> 01:38.880
And the five fingered ones
have the tremendous honour

01:38.880 --> 01:42.400
of being one part of that hoop.

01:42.400 --> 01:44.580
One of the problems
with the old story

01:44.580 --> 01:46.360
within Western
culture is that it’s

01:46.360 --> 01:48.340
perpetuated a
sense of separation

01:48.340 --> 01:50.590
between humans and the
planet, between humans

01:50.590 --> 01:51.670
and the natural world.

01:51.670 --> 01:55.930
We are one with Mother Earth,
we are one with the cosmos,

01:55.930 --> 01:57.800
we are one with the universe.

01:57.800 --> 02:00.470
There is never a disconnection.

02:00.470 --> 02:04.090
And the world is
the way it is today

02:04.090 --> 02:08.840
because of the stories we have
communicated to each other.

02:08.840 --> 02:10.794
Stories are the
library of humanity.

02:10.794 --> 02:12.420
And we need to refer
to them because

02:12.420 --> 02:15.480
we've, in essence,
captured all the wisdom we

02:15.480 --> 02:16.880
have in our stories.

02:16.880 --> 02:19.550
But we must be careful
what we wish for.

02:19.550 --> 02:25.000
For every story limits as much
as it illumines and defines.

02:25.000 --> 02:27.980
Western science
started out with a story

02:27.980 --> 02:32.560
of a non-living, meaningless,
purposeless universe.

02:32.560 --> 02:35.970
It then discovered entropy.
It said it’s all running down.

02:35.970 --> 02:38.040
Okay, this is the
bleakest creation story

02:38.040 --> 02:40.820
anyone ever thought up.

02:40.820 --> 02:43.057
It’s all a question of story.

02:43.057 --> 02:44.890
We are in trouble just
now because we do not

02:44.890 --> 02:46.590
have a good story.

02:46.590 --> 02:49.082
We are in between stories.

02:49.082 --> 02:52.800
♪ There are
many, there are many,

02:52.800 --> 02:54.492
♪ there are many voices calling.

02:58.428 --> 03:04.990
♪ Who can hear the mother,
hear the mother crying.

03:08.910 --> 03:13.320
♪ Whoa come on now, whoa
it’s time, it’s time

03:13.320 --> 03:15.280
♪ to care for Earth.

03:18.220 --> 03:23.610
♪ Whoa come on now, whoa
it’s time, it’s time

03:23.610 --> 03:25.570
♪ to care for Earth.

03:29.351 --> 03:30.850
The thought of
Thomas Berry who was

03:30.850 --> 03:33.470
an American ecological
and cosmological thinker

03:33.470 --> 03:33.990
and writer.

03:33.990 --> 03:36.020
And when I encountered
the work of Thomas Berry,

03:36.020 --> 03:38.530
and then I had the opportunity
to study with Thomas Berry

03:38.530 --> 03:40.530
and have him as a
mentor for 20 years,

03:40.530 --> 03:42.900
he was talking about
the power of worldview.

03:42.900 --> 03:45.320
He wrote an essay in 1978
called “The New Story“

03:45.320 --> 03:48.720
in which he said it’s
all a question of story.

03:48.720 --> 03:50.610
We are in trouble just
now because we do not

03:50.610 --> 03:51.610
have a good story.

03:59.050 --> 04:05.900
We have come to believe that
nature is separate from us,

04:05.900 --> 04:08.706
and we are separate from nature.

04:08.706 --> 04:13.520
Nature’s out there, and we
can do what we like to nature.

04:13.520 --> 04:15.540
We can cut down the rainforests.

04:15.540 --> 04:18.720
We can put animals
in factory farms

04:18.720 --> 04:20.540
and slaughter them as we like.

04:20.540 --> 04:22.720
We can overfish the oceans.

04:22.720 --> 04:24.370
We can pollute the rivers.

04:24.370 --> 04:26.500
We can pollute the water
and change climate.

04:26.500 --> 04:27.810
We can do what we like.

04:27.810 --> 04:30.660
But we are somehow
superior to nature.

04:30.660 --> 04:33.350
We are somehow rulers of nature.

04:33.350 --> 04:35.050
That’s the old story.

04:35.050 --> 04:39.050
The strangest of all beliefs
which is that as humans on this

04:39.050 --> 04:44.180
planet we cannot help but
destroy the planet while we are

04:44.180 --> 04:45.160
living on it.

04:45.160 --> 04:48.550
We are putting so much
pressure on the environment,

04:48.550 --> 04:51.170
so much pressure on
poor people, so much

04:51.170 --> 04:52.950
pressure on the atmosphere.

04:52.950 --> 04:53.730
Global warming.

04:53.730 --> 04:54.400
Climate change.

04:54.400 --> 04:57.650
So our glaciers were
receding very fast.

04:57.650 --> 05:02.080
And the weather changed very
quickly in the last three years

05:02.080 --> 05:03.170
for us.

05:03.170 --> 05:06.170
Even it snowed in
the desert this year.

05:06.170 --> 05:10.430
With the mining of oil,
with the shale gas industry,

05:10.430 --> 05:11.070
fracking.

05:11.070 --> 05:15.840
Chainsaws, and bulldozers,
and chemical sprays.

05:15.840 --> 05:22.830
The lungs of our planet
being destroyed at a rate

05:22.830 --> 05:26.860
that leaves one breathless.

05:26.860 --> 05:31.310
All of this for the resources
for which without we would not

05:31.310 --> 05:35.840
have laptops, we would
not have cell phones,

05:35.840 --> 05:39.230
and the many gadgets
that we depend on today.

05:39.230 --> 05:41.460
We live in a very,
very brutal system.

05:41.460 --> 05:45.020
Not only brutal toward
those that we can easily

05:45.020 --> 05:50.330
see as victims, but equally
brutal toward the perpetrators.

05:50.330 --> 05:52.440
Otherwise, how would they
become the perpetrators?

05:52.440 --> 05:55.980
You know, what has to happen
to a human being for them

05:55.980 --> 05:58.300
to do the things that
people do to each other?

05:58.300 --> 06:03.980
Every four seconds a child
in Africa is starving.

06:07.614 --> 06:14.540
In our normality,
all of us, a girl,

06:14.540 --> 06:22.700
her genital parts are cut so
she does not enjoy sexuality.

06:22.700 --> 06:24.920
A woman is raped.

06:24.920 --> 06:29.060
A woman in my country is killed
because her husband or brother

06:29.060 --> 06:33.570
is jealous—what’s called
the honour of the family.

06:33.570 --> 06:37.680
In the normality, a
field of Pachamama

06:37.680 --> 06:41.040
is spread with chemicals,
and another part of her body

06:41.040 --> 06:42.700
is getting rotten.

06:42.700 --> 06:47.120
People are being
killed as we speak here

06:47.120 --> 06:53.370
for diamonds, gold, copper,
cobalt, coltan, silver,

06:53.370 --> 06:54.620
uranium.

06:54.620 --> 06:58.020
We live in a for-profit
world, essentially.

06:58.020 --> 07:00.850
It’s a market based
economy, and success

07:00.850 --> 07:03.580
is measured by your
return on investment,

07:03.580 --> 07:07.180
by your market share, by
your level of profitability,

07:07.180 --> 07:08.660
by margins, all of these things.

07:08.660 --> 07:09.690
That’s the deal.

07:09.690 --> 07:13.140
Just the narrative
to just get a job,

07:13.140 --> 07:16.610
and make money, and play
the capitalistic game,

07:16.610 --> 07:19.380
it’s not working
for young people.

07:19.380 --> 07:22.140
Today’s young people don’t
want to just work, work, work.

07:22.140 --> 07:24.810
All the kids, we were
at war against the teachers,

07:24.810 --> 07:26.600
they were at war against us.

07:26.600 --> 07:29.880
And it was all based on
massive harm and destruction,

07:29.880 --> 07:33.650
psychological and
violent, physical harm.

07:33.650 --> 07:35.350
Because when you
grew up in gangs

07:35.350 --> 07:39.130
in a very angry,
controlled environment,

07:39.130 --> 07:42.920
I had to learn to fight
and defend myself in ways

07:42.920 --> 07:44.480
I didn’t realise I had to.

07:44.480 --> 07:47.230
Because I was black, you
know, I had this history

07:47.230 --> 07:49.750
that I had to fight for that
I did not know anything about.

07:49.750 --> 07:52.650
And we’re born with
this perception,

07:52.650 --> 08:00.180
I would call it a knowing,
that gets beaten out of us.

08:00.180 --> 08:01.610
And that’s a very
painful process,

08:01.610 --> 08:04.525
to be ejected from
a magical world.

08:04.525 --> 08:10.960
♪ Wait a minute,
is that the ocean I smell?

08:10.960 --> 08:16.974
♪ And my heart moves to the
rhythm of a big blue swell.

08:16.974 --> 08:23.446
♪ From the top of the atmosphere,
to the deep I dive,

08:23.446 --> 08:28.188
♪ and I know that our
children will survive.

08:29.746 --> 08:35.318
♪ There are things that we
can count on in our lives.

08:35.318 --> 08:37.748
♪ Wait a minute.

08:52.217 --> 08:55.199
To the story of our future.

09:00.710 --> 09:07.330
The future records written
in the fossils of this planet

09:07.330 --> 09:14.102
will actually record a time
of great turning, a time

09:14.102 --> 09:15.310
of incredible self awareness.

09:26.120 --> 09:31.330
This event, of New
Story Summit at Findhorn,

09:31.330 --> 09:34.590
is an expression of awakening.

09:34.590 --> 09:36.740
An expression of
rising consciousness,

09:36.740 --> 09:38.110
changing consciousness.

09:38.110 --> 09:41.440
A 7-day experience
of being mutually held

09:41.440 --> 09:44.190
in a radically different
way of seeing the world.

09:44.190 --> 09:46.860
The moment this
New Story Summit

09:46.860 --> 09:51.130
was announced, within a
month it was sold out.

09:51.130 --> 09:54.040
Please know that as we go
into this journey this week,

09:54.040 --> 09:58.680
we are walking in a pre-prepared
field of potentially

09:58.680 --> 10:00.260
transformational energy.

10:03.200 --> 10:06.060
The original impulse
for the summit

10:06.060 --> 10:08.370
was to see what
would happen if we

10:08.370 --> 10:11.480
got a group of people
together who are all carrying

10:11.480 --> 10:14.170
a thread of the new story.

10:14.170 --> 10:16.850
Not try to reach
a single story,

10:16.850 --> 10:19.900
but figure out what
are our common values?

10:19.900 --> 10:23.480
What are the values we are going
to base all those stories on?

10:23.480 --> 10:28.000
Love, and cooperation,
and friendly competition.

10:28.000 --> 10:32.400
We are consciously stepping
out of our comfort zone.

10:32.400 --> 10:36.140
And we do this through
creative being together,

10:36.140 --> 10:42.520
through combining all
kinds of old and new wisdom

10:42.520 --> 10:45.400
by combining the
youngest and the oldest.

10:45.400 --> 10:49.100
This isn’t just an
excursion from reality, but

10:49.100 --> 10:51.090
this is a glimpse of the future.

10:51.090 --> 10:55.170
It is amazing that people from
forty-five different countries

10:55.170 --> 10:56.510
have come to this event.

10:56.510 --> 11:01.240
My name is Visolela
Namises. I am from Namibia.

11:01.240 --> 11:05.040
[Introduction in own language]

11:05.040 --> 11:08.950
[Introduction in own language]

11:08.950 --> 11:13.800
[Introduction in own language]

11:13.800 --> 11:15.380
[Introduction in own language]

11:15.380 --> 11:19.850
My name’s Vicki Downey and I’m from
Tesugeh Oweengeh in New Mexico.

11:19.850 --> 11:26.010
[Introduction in own language]

11:26.010 --> 11:29.980
It’s really a privilege to
be here with you, particularly

11:29.980 --> 11:33.850
to be the only
non-physical person

11:33.850 --> 11:36.120
present, which I
suppose is fitting

11:36.120 --> 11:38.840
given what I want to talk about.

11:38.840 --> 11:41.520
I always come into these
events with a high amount

11:41.520 --> 11:43.920
of expectation and
this has just blown me

11:43.920 --> 11:47.000
away in terms of the
spaces that we’ve been in.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.120
What flourished
here over the years

11:49.120 --> 11:53.962
is what you see now, a
living, working community.

11:53.962 --> 11:55.670
I want you to know
that this event is not

11:55.670 --> 11:58.850
happening at a conference centre
where everything done for you

11:58.850 --> 12:02.090
is done by paid employees.

12:02.090 --> 12:04.440
The people who are harvesting
the food, the people who

12:04.440 --> 12:07.210
are cooking in the kitchen,
the people who are cleaning up,

12:07.210 --> 12:10.930
the office staff, everybody
here is part of this community.

12:10.930 --> 12:14.440
We’re all drawn here by
this impulse to co-create,

12:14.440 --> 12:17.350
to be of world service,
and to deeply listen.

12:17.350 --> 12:20.800
Our inner attunement and
cooperation with nature

12:20.800 --> 12:24.600
created an atmosphere,
a powerful note that

12:24.600 --> 12:27.020
attracted many on inner levels.

12:27.020 --> 12:30.280
We’re certainly not
perfect by any extent

12:30.280 --> 12:32.990
of the imagination. All
the stuff that happens

12:32.990 --> 12:34.960
in the world is happening here.

12:34.960 --> 12:38.130
But why I like to
be here is that I

12:38.130 --> 12:42.260
like what we do with that,
how we deal with all that.

12:42.260 --> 12:44.530
We were asked to
have no publicity

12:44.530 --> 12:48.830
and invite no one here, and
yet people kept arriving.

12:48.830 --> 12:52.050
When I first arrived in
Findhorn 40 years ago,

12:52.050 --> 12:58.160
I knew the community had a
gift to give the larger world

12:58.160 --> 13:01.450
and that’s why I stayed.

13:01.450 --> 13:06.040
40 years later, I still feel
that way, indeed even more so,

13:06.040 --> 13:08.536
in part, at least,
because of this is event.

13:08.536 --> 13:09.910
These kind of
gatherings give me

13:09.910 --> 13:12.930
hope that there’s so much
energy and possibility,

13:12.930 --> 13:16.090
to host our pain,
to host our joy,

13:16.090 --> 13:18.750
and to bring all of those things
into a weaving that may really

13:18.750 --> 13:22.070
serve us as a humanity
and serve this Earth.

13:22.070 --> 13:28.070
I’ve seen people of many
nations grieving together.

13:31.240 --> 13:35.220
And I’ve seen people of many
nations dancing together.

13:38.172 --> 13:43.700
And I've seen indigenous
people from many nations

13:43.700 --> 13:50.970
coming together and
taking us in a ceremony,

13:50.970 --> 14:04.160
weaving so beautifully, no
ego, sharing feathers, fully

14:04.160 --> 14:08.045
in service of our
grieving of our hearts.

14:14.040 --> 14:16.520
Thank you for the simplicity.

14:16.520 --> 14:18.760
Thank you for the co-creation.

14:18.760 --> 14:20.094
Thank you for our co-creation.

14:24.010 --> 14:24.700
May we continue.

14:28.230 --> 14:30.230
The thing that has struck
me the most this week

14:30.230 --> 14:32.850
is how wonderful and
wondrous this group of people

14:32.850 --> 14:36.570
is and how magical this event is.

14:36.570 --> 14:38.810
But not from a perspective
of us creating a meta

14:38.810 --> 14:42.000
story for the world,
but from a perspective

14:42.000 --> 14:45.420
of each one of us looking at
our own individual stories.

14:45.420 --> 14:49.550
In personal transformation
we go through a period

14:49.550 --> 14:52.790
where nothing works,
there’s nothing out there,

14:52.790 --> 14:56.170
it’s a total void, we
don’t know where to go.

14:56.170 --> 15:01.130
And now, this is happening at
a collective level in groups.

15:01.130 --> 15:04.440
And we really don’t
have the skills yet

15:04.440 --> 15:08.110
to learn how to
get through that.

15:08.110 --> 15:11.510
But we learned a little
bit at this conference

15:11.510 --> 15:17.080
because on Tuesday night
the whole group broke.

15:17.080 --> 15:21.150
Everybody had different needs,
and wants, and all of this.

15:21.150 --> 15:23.830
And there was an opposition
between the old story

15:23.830 --> 15:26.010
and the new story,
which is going

15:26.010 --> 15:29.610
to be the big
opposition in the world.

15:29.610 --> 15:31.850
There it was, right
in front of us.

15:31.850 --> 15:33.804
[Laughter]

15:33.804 --> 15:36.470
I don’t know if any of you felt
like that in the last few days,

15:36.470 --> 15:45.730
the seeds like—It might have been,

15:45.730 --> 15:49.030
why are they stopping
that woman from speaking?

15:49.030 --> 15:53.660
That is the essential
truth we all need to hear.

15:53.660 --> 15:56.170
Or, simultaneously
in some other part

15:56.170 --> 15:59.920
of the audience someone
saying, why have they

15:59.920 --> 16:02.180
not stopped her yet?

16:10.320 --> 16:14.550
Tick, tick, tick, tick,
tick, tick, talk everybody.

16:14.550 --> 16:17.270
And meanwhile, somewhere
else, somebody is thinking,

16:17.270 --> 16:20.640
I wonder what’s for lunch today.

16:20.640 --> 16:24.120
We didn’t do a very good
job of getting through that.

16:24.120 --> 16:28.590
So two nights, two days
later, what happens again?

16:28.590 --> 16:30.790
Another eruption.

16:30.790 --> 16:33.320
Because we have
a situation here.

16:33.320 --> 16:35.930
We came in this
morning with a plan.

16:35.930 --> 16:39.201
What a crazy idea.

16:39.201 --> 16:40.700
We thought, we’ll
just kind of tweak

16:40.700 --> 16:42.370
what we had yesterday
on the agenda,

16:42.370 --> 16:43.953
and then we’ll know
where we’re going.

16:43.953 --> 16:49.050
And then I walk in and go
ah—this is interesting.

16:49.050 --> 16:50.530
This is a little different.

16:50.530 --> 16:52.600
We don’t know.

16:52.600 --> 16:55.930
I’m sitting here, as we say at
Findhorn, my heart is pounding.

16:55.930 --> 16:58.265
I’m really angry that
something suddenly

16:58.265 --> 16:59.750
seems to be taken over.

16:59.750 --> 17:05.150
How many people don’t want to
go to workshops in the format

17:05.150 --> 17:06.367
that we had yesterday?

17:06.367 --> 17:10.579
Who does want to
go into open space?

17:10.579 --> 17:16.829
You know, I’m just seeing,
like, this kind of habitual

17:16.829 --> 17:21.000
internalised acquiescence to,
like, waiting for somebody else

17:21.000 --> 17:22.002
to do it for us.

17:22.002 --> 17:24.460
As Charles said, we don’t need
to wait for permission now.

17:24.460 --> 17:25.835
But of course,
there’s a tendency

17:25.835 --> 17:26.800
to wait for permission.

17:26.800 --> 17:29.230
Anybody who wants to
right now can come down.

17:29.230 --> 17:32.760
Either find the paper you had
yesterday, find a post-it,

17:32.760 --> 17:35.490
write your name, claim a space.

17:41.190 --> 17:43.912
I know it’s been rocky
at times, but I just

17:43.912 --> 17:45.870
want to appreciate our
willingness to, kind of,

17:45.870 --> 17:47.320
flow with what needs to happen.

17:47.320 --> 17:50.280
I think we’ve got to a
reasonable place, a good place,

17:50.280 --> 17:52.860
actually, where a lot
of needs are honoured.

17:52.860 --> 17:59.110
So, I’m going to pass it
to you to close our space.

17:59.110 --> 18:03.630
On the instrument,
unlike pianos and guitars,

18:03.630 --> 18:06.190
all the notes are connected
by the skin of the shell.

18:08.700 --> 18:13.000
So when one note is activated,
the whole shell is vibrating

18:13.000 --> 18:15.890
and it’s connecting with
all the other notes.

18:15.890 --> 18:18.220
And sometimes it
activates the other notes

18:18.220 --> 18:20.940
so I thought it would be
a nice way to come back

18:20.940 --> 18:21.890
into being together.

